Global Next-Generation Data Storage Market Insights
Next-Generation Data Storage Market size was valued at USD 20 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 50 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 15% from 2024 to 2030.

Next-Generation Data Storage Market Overview
The global Next-Generation Data Storage market is experiencing substantial growth, with a projected market size reaching USD 150 billion by 2028, driven by increasing data volumes and the adoption of cloud-based storage solutions. This surge is attributed to the growing need for scalable, efficient, and secure data storage technologies across industries like healthcare, retail, and IT services. The market is further fueled by advancements in technologies such as AI, machine learning, and blockchain, which require large-scale data storage infrastructure. As digitalization accelerates, organizations are focusing on improving data management capabilities to meet the growing demand for faster data retrieval and processing speeds.

